{
  "local_port": 47000,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What's the best applicant tracking system for a small staffing agency?",
  "response": "Choosing the best applicant tracking system (ATS) for a small staffing agency depends on your specific needs, budget, and the features you prioritize. Here are some top ATS options that are well-suited for small staffing agencies:\n\n### 1. **Bullhorn**\n   - **Why it\u2019s great for staffing agencies**: Bullhorn is specifically designed for staffing and recruiting firms. It offers robust features like candidate and client management, job posting, and integration with job boards.\n   - **Key features**: CRM, job management, candidate tracking, email and calendar integration, reporting.\n   - **Pricing**: Custom pricing based on the size of the agency.\n\n### 2. **Zoho Recruit**\n   - **Why it\u2019s great for staffing agencies**: Zoho Recruit is a flexible and affordable option that offers both cloud-based and on-premise solutions. It\u2019s highly customizable and integrates well with other Zoho products.\n   - **Key features**: Candidate sourcing, resume parsing, interview scheduling, vendor management, and reporting.\n   - **Pricing**: Starts at $25/user/month (billed annually).\n\n### 3. **JobDiva**\n   - **Why it\u2019s great for staffing agencies**: JobDiva is a powerful ATS with a strong focus on staffing and recruitment. It offers advanced AI-driven features for candidate matching and job posting.\n   - **Key features**: Candidate matching, job posting, CRM, analytics, and integrations with major job boards.\n   - **Pricing**: Custom pricing based on needs.\n\n### 4. **ClearCompany**\n   - **Why it\u2019s great for staffing agencies**: ClearCompany is known for its user-friendly interface and comprehensive suite of recruiting tools. It\u2019s ideal for agencies looking for an all-in-one solution.\n   - **Key features**: Talent acquisition, onboarding, performance management, and analytics.\n   - **Pricing**: Custom pricing based on the number of users and features.\n\n### 5. **Recruitee**\n   - **Why it\u2019s great for staffing agencies**: Recruitee is a modern ATS that\u2019s easy to use and offers strong collaboration features, making it ideal for small teams.\n   - **Key features**: Team collaboration, candidate sourcing, job board integrations, and analytics.\n   - **Pricing**: Starts at $199/month for up to 5 users.\n\n### 6. **Hirebridge**\n   - **Why it\u2019s great for staffing agencies**: Hirebridge offers a comprehensive ATS with a focus on staffing and recruiting. It\u2019s known for its flexibility and scalability.\n   - **Key features**: Applicant tracking, onboarding, CRM, and job board integrations.\n   - **Pricing**: Custom pricing based on needs.\n\n### 7. **Lever**\n   - **Why it\u2019s great for staffing agencies**: Lever is a modern ATS that combines applicant tracking with CRM capabilities. It\u2019s ideal for agencies looking for a more holistic approach to recruitment.\n   - **Key features**: Candidate relationship management, interview scheduling, collaboration tools, and analytics.\n   - **Pricing**: Custom pricing based on needs.\n\n### 8. **Workable**\n   - **Why it\u2019s great for staffing agencies**: Workable is a popular ATS known for its ease of use and quick setup. It\u2019s great for small staffing agencies that need to get up and running quickly.\n   - **Key features**: Job posting, candidate sourcing, interview scheduling, and team collaboration.\n   - **Pricing**: Starts at $99/month for up to 20 employees.\n\n### 9. **BambooHR**\n   - **Why it\u2019s great for staffing agencies**: BambooHR is an all-in-one HR software that includes a strong ATS. It\u2019s ideal for small agencies that need more than just recruiting tools.\n   - **Key features**: Applicant tracking, onboarding, HR management, and reporting.\n   - **Pricing**: Custom pricing based on needs.\n\n### 10. **Fountain**\n   - **Why it\u2019s great for staffing agencies**: Fountain is designed for high-volume recruiting, making it ideal for staffing agencies handling large numbers of candidates.\n   - **Key features**: Candidate sourcing, SMS recruiting, interview scheduling, and analytics.\n   - **Pricing**: Custom pricing based on needs.\n\n### Considerations When Choosing an ATS:\n- **Ease of Use**: Ensure the system is user-friendly and easy to navigate.\n- **Integration**: Look for systems that integrate with your existing tools (e.g., job boards, email, CRM).\n- **Scalability**: Choose a system that can grow with your agency.\n- **Support**: Consider the level of customer support and training provided.\n- **Cost**: Make sure the pricing fits within your budget, including any additional fees for extra features or users.\n\n### Conclusion:\nFor a small staffing agency, **Zoho Recruit** and **Workable** are excellent starting points due to their affordability and ease of use. If you\u2019re looking for a more specialized solution, **Bullhorn** or **JobDiva** might be more appropriate. Always consider a demo or trial to ensure the system meets your specific needs before committing.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
